Program: Outlook
Title: The Bullfighter who Switched Sides
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p044pvy8
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 23 Aug 2016
Álvaro Múnera was a bullfighter in Colombia until a dramatic development in his own life. Marisa Monte is one of Brazil's most successful musicians. Nedra Bonds is known for a very unusual form of political protest - stitched quilts. Sanjoy Hazarika set up a floating clinic to bring healthcare to island-dwellers in Assam, northern India. (Photo: A bullfighter and bull. Credit: Luis Robayo/AFP/Getty Images) Show less